description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Occupational Therapist Fixed Term 12 months maternity cover&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sutton Coldfield, West Midlands&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time 37.5hours per week with flexibility for the right candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary based on experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit a confident, organised, motivated and creative Occupational Therapist (OT) to work alongside our current OTs and OT Assistants, in an established multi-disciplinary team at Newbridge House, a specialist eating disorder inpatient service for young people aged 8-18. Working hours are Monday – Friday with flexibility between the hours of 8am and 7pm. The OT service utilises the Model of Human Occupation framework to provide a comprehensive assessment and treatment program. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Individual work to explore how an individual’s motivation, habits, skills and home/social life is impacting on their day to day life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identifying barriers and empowering young people to set goals and make positive changes to their lifestyle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facilitation of a range of therapeutic and skills based groups, including meal preparation, social eating and creative art.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community outreach to develop social skills, managing anxiety, lifestyle rebalance and return to home, school and college.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous experience of working with young people with eating disorders, or in CAMHS is desirable but not essential, as in-house training and clinical supervision is provided. A full UK driving licence is essential, as is the use of a car for business purposes. The post is full time, but part time will be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 17th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please email deborah.hartland&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;@newbridge-health.org.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; if you would like an informal discussion about the post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;PLEASE NOTE that this vacancy will be closed as soon as sufficient applications are received. It is strongly advised that you complete and return your application form as soon as possible in order to avoid disappointment. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
